HEADWORD: Artiad
<hw>Ar"ti*ad</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ even, fr.
<?/ exactly.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Even; not odd; -- said of
elementary substances and of radicals the valence of which is divisible
by two without a remainder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

